explanation for datasets:

### on-street-parking-bay-sensors.json
on-street parking sensor data showing location and usage status (occupied or not)
source: https://data.melbourne.vic.gov.au/explore/dataset/on-street-parking-bay-sensors/information/?%3D%3D

### sign-plates-located-in-each-parking-zones (csv and json)
A sign plate is where the parking restrictions are displayed. 
Can be used to add more information about on-street parkign spot (if needed)
source: https://data.melbourne.vic.gov.au/explore/dataset/sign-plates-located-in-each-parking-zone/information/?

### Off-street car parks with capacity and type (csv and json)
The number of off-street car parking spaces/capacity per property. 
This dataset has been wrangled and cleaned, resulting only commercial parking type and retrieving only Melbourne CBD parking spot only 
source: https://data.melbourne.vic.gov.au/explore/dataset/off-street-car-parks-with-capacity-and-type/table/?disjunctive.clue_small_area&disjunctive.parking_type&disjunctive.block_id&disjunctive.parking_spaces&location=13,-37.81298,144.94529&basemap=mbs-7a7333
